$interpreted: Dagger: Furygrowl? What happened? Why so hasty?
Furygrowl: I caught wind of a rumor...
Dagger: Outta my way. Let me in!
Crushfang: It's late now. You have something to say?
Dagger: Damn right I have something to say! What's that on your table?
Crushfang: Proposal from Theodore himself.
Dagger: Of course he is asking us to surrender. What's written there?
Crushfang: Theodore promises that as long as we hand Angelia over, Kingdom of Sun will no longer harass the Bears.
Dagger: You believe that nonsense?
Crushfang: At least Theodore has a written promise as evidence. The princess, on the other hand, can't promise that she will be able to defeat Theodore.
Crushfang: If we bet on the wrong side, it will be a catastrophic disaster for the Bears.
Dagger: So you want to betray Angelia because of that?
Crushfang: ... I won't make rash decision and accept Theodore's proposal without giving it thought. However, as Chieftain of the Bears, I must consider everything.
Crushfang: Only then can I make a decision that is the best path for the future of the Bears.
Dagger: This path better not be one that's paved by abandoning the Bears' dignity!
Naya: Dagger, what business do you have with us at this time of the night?
Dagger: You sure there are only three of you here?
Sione: Yes, just as you requested...
Dagger: Besides you guys, don't know who I can trust now anymore...be it Hyde, or even Chieftain...
Angelia: Sir Dagger, what do you want to tell us?
Dagger: I'm here to warn you guys. Chieftain and Theodore have already...
Crushfang: Just as expected; you indeed helped us lure out the princess.
Crushfang: If princess was hiding in the Sunshine Infantry, things may have been more troublesome.
Angelia: What exactly is going on here...?
Dagger: Crushfang, are you serious...!
Crushfang: I have said before, I will choose the future that is best for the Bears.
Dagger: Furygrowl, you too...
Furygrowl: They treat us Bears as nothing more than tools to defeat Theodore. If the princess doesn't give a damn about Bear soldier casualties,
Furygrowl: neither should we honor our promises!
Naya: You bastards!
Crushfang: Bear soldiers, capture Angelia, alive!
Dagger: ...*heavy breathing*...I...will never...abandon...the Bears' dignity...
Crushfang: Princess, please stop this pointless resistance...
